.so ../bk-macros
.TH "bk sane" "\*[BKVER]" %E% "\*(BC" "\*(UM"
.SH NAME
bk sane \- check for various \*[BK] requirements
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bk sane
.[B] \-c
.SH DESCRIPTION
Run this command from within a repository to check whether the repository
is configured correctly.
.B bk\ sane
checks for a valid hostname, username,
and permissions on various metadata directories, and the ability to lock
the idcache.  If everything is sane, the command exits with a 0 exit
status and no output.  If there are problems, a detailed error message
is displayed on stderr and a non-zero exit status is returned.
.LP
When submitting bug reports, please include the output of this command
run with the 
.B \-c
option.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c
In addition to the basic checks, run a full repository integrity check.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.LP
.B bk sane
returns exit status:
.TP
0
on success.
.tp
1
on failure.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.SA check
.SA sendbug
